                                                                                                                       7                                        Bhutia roots for Brazil
            OUR CORRESPONDENT AMP; AGENCIES            Bhutia in Mumbai on Wednesday. (PTI)                           
	Mumbai: Bhaichung Bhutia thinks Brazil would do better this time in the World Cup.         
	At a promotional here on Wednesday, Bhutia also stressed on the need to provide better facilities for the youngsters.         
	In Europe, even small clubs produce players for teams like Manchester United. They train talented players and promote them as well. Same should be done in India to encourage budding footballers, Bhutia said.         
	Actor John Abraham, who was also present, said: The corporate initiative would help hunt football talent in the country. He said he was ready to play charity matches to promote the game.         
	As per the scheme, Castrol would offer an opportunity to 30 lucky winners to accompany John to South Africa for an all expenses paid trip during the Cup.                                                                                                                     
